      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your previous panic attack doesn't mean this time is the same, and trusting your doctor's past reassurance is dangerous when symptoms feel different. You should not ignore new or worsening chest pressure, even if you've had anxiety before, because heart issues can mimic panic attacks. Please call emergency services now to get checked out immediately; it is the only safe way to rule out a heart attack.",
      "source": "target",
